	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">That is a really cool set, but most of them don't have any spaces between the chars, so they'd run together as tiles.</div>
<br />The IBM Monochrome Display Adapter had a hack to improve the apparent resolution of text: tiles of 9x14 pixels were stored as 8x14 in the card's ROM. Most tiles had a blank column of pixels added at the right side, except for tiles $C0 through $DF (mostly box drawing tiles) which duplicated the right column of pixels. The 14- and 16-line text modes in EGA and VGA kept the feature.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


