	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Today, I was at a craft store, and here's what I found:
<br />
<br /><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7m1jIK_Ec5Q" class="postlink"><img src="http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/41oNSxO%2BTJL._AA260_.jpg" alt="Image" /></a>
<br />
<br />But more to the point, you can find bitmap fonts, some of them multicolor, in the "ABC" books in the cross-stitch section. A lot of them are collections of drop-caps, but there are a lot that could be turned into 8x8, 8x16, or small proportional bitmap fonts. For example, <em>Precious Moments: Welcome Home Baby</em> has this rendition of Wasted Collection:
<br /><img src="http://pineight.com/mw/images/b/b6/Wasted_Collection_12.png" alt="Image" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
